        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 3:38PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles north of Waynesville, or near Lake Junaluska. This storm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Waynesville, Canton, Lake Junaluska, Clyde, Smoky
Mountains-Cataloochee, Maggie Valley, Cove Creek, and Fines Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
